&#xa0;
[normal]The importance of the Select Committee Process &amp; The Wright Reforms[bold]“Any member of a select committee whose cumulative attendance during a Session is below 60% should be automatically discharged at the end of that Session”
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Attendance generally above 60%[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Legitimate Absence[bold]Recommended Penalty System as a form of incentive to attend[bold]MPs enter Parliament to make a difference or to scrutinise the government; if they are prevented from doing this then they will look to eradicate any behaviour that leads to this; this will surely mean more MPs feeling incentivised to either attend all possible select committee meetings or contributing via post-meeting reports in their absence.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Concluding Remarks[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]20 December 2013
